Subject: Is Your Halloween Costume Racist?
 
By Maureen O'Connor

[1]Is Your Halloween Costume Racist?
     Links:
       1. http://gawker.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=251e609e1dba3888b86c21cc8&id=8544c081ef&e=ec29360622

   Some Halloween costumes [2]offend the senses. Some are [3]just plain
   offensive. Here's a handy guide to 12 racially charged Halloween costumes,
   whether you can get away with wearing them, and what to do if you
   accidentally bought a racist one.
     Links:
       2. http://gawker.us1.list-manage1.com/track/click?u=251e609e1dba3888b86c21cc8&id=8bb309113a&e=ec29360622
       3. http://gawker.us1.list-manage1.com/track/click?u=251e609e1dba3888b86c21cc8&id=39ffd8a212&e=ec29360622

   _[4]'Seductive Squaw'_
   Do not wear this costume. First, no matter what the [5]makers of this
   costume tell you, "squaw" is not a acceptable term. Second, when the
   entirety of your costume is "I am a person of a different race, LOL," that
   qualifies as a racist costume. If you accidentally bought this costume,
   chuck it. Possible exception: You are going in a large group that includes
   Peter Pan, Wendy, and Tinkerbell. Just make sure you _do not_ lose sight of
   the group, and be aware that seducing a man dressed as cowboys will be
   misconstrued. [Yandy via [7]TBD, [8]Yandy]
     Links:
       4. http://gawker.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=251e609e1dba3888b86c21cc8&id=37b5542ef2&e=ec29360622
       5. http://gawker.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=251e609e1dba3888b86c21cc8&id=64e9176d6e&e=ec29360622
       6. http://gawker.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=251e609e1dba3888b86c21cc8&id=78cdb625a3&e=ec29360622
       7. http://gawker.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=251e609e1dba3888b86c21cc8&id=0ab61e3712&e=ec29360622
       8. http://gawker.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=251e609e1dba3888b86c21cc8&id=1a30b4d0f5&e=ec29360622

   _Eskimos_
   On one hand, they're not called "Eskimo" anymore, but "Inuit." On the other,
   this costume is so far removed from its source material that it's hard to
   draw a straight line between it and the mockery of native northern peoples.
   The main problem with this costume is that it's nonsensical. Only wear it if
   you plan on doing a ton of blow. [Yandy]
     Links:
       9. http://gawker.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=251e609e1dba3888b86c21cc8&id=2c9d135eab&e=ec29360622

   _Geisha_
   Geishas are a cohesive enough cultural phenomenon, and if you were to
   actually dress like a geisha--[10]with multiple layers of floor-length
   kimono and little white toe socks--that is fine. But are you _really_ going
   to dress like a geisha, or are you going to dress like a teenage victim of
   sexual trafficking giving happy endings in some crummy massage parlor in San
   Jose? You can probably get away with this kind of "geisha," too, but I urge
   you to resist. If you want to be a whore for Halloween, just be a whore, and
   skip the creepy racial overtones. Possible exception: This "[11]Japanese
   Entertainer Costume" is almost--but not entirely--self-aware. [Yandy]
     Links:
       10. http://gawker.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=251e609e1dba3888b86c21cc8&id=859b24305f&e=ec29360622
       11. http://gawker.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=251e609e1dba3888b86c21cc8&id=a1a2d3e4e0&e=ec29360622
       12. http://gawker.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=251e609e1dba3888b86c21cc8&id=fca66249e4&e=ec29360622

   _'Asian Doll'_
   Whereas geishas occupy a grey area ([13]Oscar-winning movies have that
   effect), mishmash pan-Asian "doll" costumes get a resounding "nay." Ditto
   "[14]Asian Costume," "[15]Sexy Asian Girl," and this "[16]Chinese Take Out
   Costume." (That last one is just begging for gross jokes about "eating
   out.") Do not wear these costumes. Possible exception: You are an Asian
   female who likes to spend Halloween confronting fetishistic creeps and
   making them uncomfortable. Proceed with caution, though, because that joke
   can backfire. [Yandy]
     Links:
       13. http://gawker.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=251e609e1dba3888b86c21cc8&id=6e0bd941c9&e=ec29360622
