       17. http://gawker.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=251e609e1dba3888b86c21cc8&id=ad61394c10&e=ec29360622

   _Vikings_
   Vikings don't exist anymore, so it's fine to dress up like them. Bigotry is
   acceptable when it's about ancient peoples of yore. We know it's OK to dress
   up like Vikings because, whereas people are always up in arms about sports
   teams with Native American mascots, nobody cares at all about the Minnesota
   Vikings' mascot, unless it's for the purpose of a Brett Favre joke. Which
   reminds me: If you dress up like a Viking, be prepared to be accosted by a
   bunch of [18]exposed-penis Favres all night. [Yandy, [20]Yandy]
     Links:
       18. http://gawker.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=251e609e1dba3888b86c21cc8&id=3b6e2a161e&e=ec29360622
       19. http://gawker.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=251e609e1dba3888b86c21cc8&id=caa3b2f139&e=ec29360622
       20. http://gawker.us1.list-manage.com/track/click?u=251e609e1dba3888b86c21cc8&id=07e99a9461&e=ec29360622

   _[21]'Harem Girl'_
   Do you really want to be in a harem, a female plaything of Middle Eastern
   polygamy? As long as the harem pant trend is going strong, I guess we should
   address this: Do not dress as a "harem girl," especially if your costume
   requires some inappropriately sexualized approximation of hijab. You may,
   however, dress as the main character from [22]I Dream of Jeannie. She was
   just a pan-Orientalist white girl, anyway. The "[23]Playboy Harem Girl
   Costume," meanwhile, is unintentionally funny. You can wear that if you're
   doing some kind of cheeky take on _The Girls Next Door_. [24]Bigamy on TV:
   [25]So hot right now.
   [Yandy, [27]Yandy]
